{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-doc-page-template-tsx","path":"/docs/hotchocolate","result":{"data":{"file":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/hotchocolate/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Introduction"},"html":"<p><em>Hot Chocolate</em> is an open-source <em>GraphQL</em> server that is compliant with the newest <em>GraphQL</em> 2020 spec. This makes Hot Chocolate compatible to all <em>GraphQL</em> compliant clients like <em>Strawberry Shake</em>, <em>Relay</em> or <em>Apollo Client</em> and to a variety of tools.</p>\n<p><em>Hot Chocolate</em> takes the complexity away from building a fully fledged GraphQL server and lets you focus on delivering the next big thing.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/e8950/platform.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Platform\"\n        title=\"Platform\"\n        src=\"/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/5a190/platform.png\"\n        srcset=\"/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/772e8/platform.png 200w,\n/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/e17e5/platform.png 400w,\n/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/5a190/platform.png 800w,\n/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/c1b63/platform.png 1200w,\n/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/29007/platform.png 1600w,\n/hotchocolate/static/830b8676a0907f2d43f104ae37724d7d/e8950/platform.png 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You can use <em>Hot Chocolate Server</em> as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A stand-alone ASP.NET Core GraphQL Server.</li>\n<li>A serverless Azure Function or Amazon Lambda that serves up a spec compliant GraphQL server.</li>\n<li>A Gateway for a federated data graph both for our own <em>Hot Chocolate Stitching</em> or for <em>Apollo Federation</em>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Hot Chocolate</em> is easy to setup and takes the clutter away.</p>\n<p>We update <em>Hot Chocolate</em> continuously and implement new spec features as they hit draft status. This lets you pick up new GraphQL features incrementally.\n...\n...\n...</p>","tableOfContents":""}},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://chillicream.com","repositoryUrl":"https://github.com/ChilliCream/hotchocolate","tools":{"slack":"https://join.slack.com/t/hotchocolategraphql/shared_invite/enQtNTA4NjA0ODYwOTQ0LTViMzA2MTM4OWYwYjIxYzViYmM0YmZhYjdiNzBjOTg2ZmU1YmMwNDZiYjUyZWZlMzNiMTk1OWUxNWZhMzQwY2Q"}}},"config":{"products":[{"path":"hotchocolate","title":"Hot Chocolate","description":"Configure a GraphQL server to fetch data from multiple data sources.","items":[{"path":"index","title":"Introduction","items":null},{"path":"getting-started","title":"Getting Started","items":null},{"path":"api-reference","title":"API Reference","items":[{"path":"index","title":"API Reference"},{"path":"batching-and-caching","title":"Batching & Caching"},{"path":"filtering","title":"Filtering"}]}]},{"path":"bananacakepop","title":"Banana Cake Pop","description":"Use this GUI to get deep insights from any GraphQL endpoint.","items":[{"path":"index","title":"Introduction","items":null}]},{"path":"strawberryshake","title":"Strawberry Shake","description":"Configure a GraphQL client in .Net to fetch data from multiple GraphQL endpoints.","items":[{"path":"index","title":"Introduction","items":null}]},{"path":"marshmellowpie","title":"Marshmellow Pie","description":"Configure a GraphQL registry to keep track of any GraphQL server and client.","items":[{"path":"index","title":"Introduction","items":null}]},{"path":"greendonut","title":"Green Donut","description":"Configure data loaders and caching for GraphQL endpoints.","items":[{"path":"index","title":"Introduction","items":null}]}]}},"pageContext":{"originPath":"hotchocolate/index.md"}}}